text: It is amazing how so many with pseudonyms are so smart and confident. Me... I am not so confident but unlike some I dont worship at the altar of price momentum I try to take advantage of it.

I am a fundamental investor - thus far the critics of a $TSLA short have not mentioned a thing about the fundie headwinds. Traders know much about price but little about value - to paraphrase Buffett. I will stick with my analysis which can be found on @realmoney.
I dont make sure term projections on a stock like $TSLA.

You are correct. On Nov 16 the S&P inclusion $TSLA $408 - now $585. I was referencing when we were short the last time . 8/28 $TSLA $463 traded to $329 on 9/9. For a loss of almost $140/shae. Time flies when we are having fun.

There only two places where we hear this nonsense and where investment mistakes are never admitted to - Fin TV and Twitter. And the bows are generally taken by those shrouded in anonymity in the cheap seats and not on the playing field.

I start small and scale on strength with a multi month short timeframe. Frankly, you are guessing. How do you explain the $140/share loss in a few days (which we captured) after the S and p announcement was made a few weeks ago?
I use many of the large brokerage firms. I rarely have a borrow issue.
